#. type: Title
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Quarkus Insights #251: Faster Startup with IBM Semeru Runtimes and OpenJ9"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: synopsis
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark Stoodley explains how IBM Semeru Runtimes and the Eclipse OpenJ9 JVM deliver faster startup times and lower memory footprint through shared classes cache technology, and how Quarkus makes it easy to take advantage of these benefits."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "This summary was generated using AI, reviewed by humans - https://youtube.com/live/ql0wK79DxtY[watch the video] for the full story."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Episode 251 of Quarkus Insights explored how developers can achieve faster startup times and reduced memory footprint by using https://developer.ibm.com/languages/java/semeru-runtimes/[IBM Semeru Runtimes] with Quarkus. Mark Stoodley, Chief Architect for Java at IBM and project co-lead for https://www.eclipse.org/openj9/[Eclipse OpenJ9], joined the show to explain the technology behind these performance improvements and how Quarkus has made it trivially easy to take advantage of them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ql0wK79DxtY\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "What is IBM Semeru Runtimes?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "IBM Semeru Runtimes is a Java distribution built by IBM that has been used in hundreds of product releases since 2006. It is based on https://openjdk.org/[OpenJDK] class libraries but uses the Eclipse OpenJ9 JVM instead of HotSpot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Key characteristics include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**100% open source** - All development happens in the Eclipse OpenJ9 and https://www.eclipse.org/omr/[Eclipse OMR] projects"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Freely available** - No features behind paywalls, with quarterly updates for Java 8, 11, 17, 21, and 26"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Broad platform support** - Runs on x86, ARM64, Power, and Z mainframe architectures"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Production proven** - Used by a significant fraction of the Fortune 500"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark emphasized that despite misconceptions, Semeru is not just for IBM's Power and mainframe platforms. It runs very well on x86 and ARM64, supporting the full range of platforms where IBM software needs to run."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "The Eclipse OpenJ9 JVM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Eclipse OpenJ9 is the JVM technology that powers Semeru Runtimes. Originally developed in the 1990s for embedded devices like cell phones and oscilloscopes, it was designed from the start to be memory-efficient and fast-starting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "A Different Design Philosophy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "OpenJ9 takes a more balanced approach to performance optimization compared to HotSpot:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Multiple performance metrics matter** - Not just raw throughput, but also startup time, memory footprint, ramp-up time, and disk space"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Optimizing for one metric can hurt others** - The team carefully balances improvements across all dimensions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**The last 10% of raw speed might be better spent elsewhere** - Dramatic improvements in startup or memory may provide more value than marginal throughput gains"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "This philosophy has made OpenJ9 particularly well-suited for cloud deployments where startup time and memory efficiency directly impact cost."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Key Technical Innovations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark highlighted several architectural decisions that distinguish OpenJ9:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**ROM/RAM Separation** - Internal data structures are carefully separated into read-only and read-write components, enabling efficient sharing across JVM instances."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Single JIT Compiler** - Unlike HotSpot's C1/C2 model, OpenJ9 uses a single adaptive compiler with multiple optimization levels (cold, warm, hot, very hot, scorching) based on a temperature metaphor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**JIT as a Service** - The compiler can run as a separate server process, allowing multiple JVM clients to share compilation resources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Single Source for All Java Versions** - The same JVM codebase is built into Java 8, 11, 17, 21, 25, and 26, enabling innovations to reach all supported versions simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "The Shared Classes Cache: The Secret Sauce"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "The centerpiece of the episode was OpenJ9's shared classes cache technology, which has been available since Java 5 (2005)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "How It Works"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "The shared classes cache is a memory-mapped file that stores:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Loaded classes** - Avoiding the cost of class loading on subsequent runs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Profile data** - Information about how the application behaves"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**JIT compiled code** - Pre-compiled methods that can be loaded ~100x faster than JIT compilation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "When you run a Java application with `-Xshareclasses`, OpenJ9 automatically creates and populates this cache. On subsequent \"warm\" runs, the JVM loads classes and compiled code directly from the cache, dramatically reducing startup time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Training Runs and Warm Runs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "The model requires a \"training run\" (cold run) to populate the cache, followed by \"warm runs\" that benefit from the cached data. This two-phase approach has historically been a challenge for container deployments, where each container start might be a cold run."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark acknowledged this limitation and noted that the team is working on:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Improving first-run performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Providing pre-populated caches for common frameworks"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Making it easier to perform training runs during container builds"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Layered Caches for Containers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "One of the most interesting features is the cache's layered architecture, which mirrors container layers:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**JDK layer** - Pre-populated classes and code from the JDK"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Framework layer** - Classes and code from frameworks like Quarkus or application servers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Application layer** - Application-specific classes and code"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "This design enables efficient container distribution since only the top layer changes between application updates, and it avoids copy-on-write memory overhead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Performance Improvements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark shared benchmark data showing significant improvements with Semeru compared to HotSpot:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Startup time** - Dramatic reductions, especially on warm runs with a populated cache"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Memory footprint** - 18-50% lower memory usage, with some workloads showing 3x improvements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Ramp-up time** - Faster time to peak performance, especially in resource-constrained environments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "These improvements are sustained across the application lifecycle, not just at startup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Quarkus Integration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "The https://quarkus.io/blog/semeru-scc/[recent work to integrate Semeru with Quarkus] makes it trivially easy to take advantage of these benefits."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Developers can enable shared classes cache support with a single property:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "When running Quarkus tests with `@QuarkusIntegrationTest`, the test execution automatically serves as the training run, populating the cache with realistic application behavior. This means good tests naturally lead to good cache population without extra effort."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Comparing with Project Leyden"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark provided a point-in-time comparison between OpenJ9's shared classes cache and https://openjdk.org/projects/leyden/[Project Leyden], the OpenJDK effort for ahead-of-time optimization:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Similarities:**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Both use training runs to improve subsequent executions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Both create archives/caches that must be distributed with applications"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Key Differences:**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Maturity** - OpenJ9's cache has been production-ready since 2005; Leyden is still under development"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Class loader support** - OpenJ9 supports application class loaders; Leyden currently only supports bootstrap loaders"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Flexibility** - OpenJ9's cache works transparently; Leyden requires explicit cache management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Compiled code** - OpenJ9 caches JIT code today; Leyden's AOT compilation is still in development"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Multi-application support** - OpenJ9 caches can be shared across multiple applications; Leyden uses single-application archives"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Container layers** - OpenJ9's layered cache design maps naturally to container layers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark emphasized this is a point-in-time comparison and both technologies continue to evolve."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "When to Choose Semeru Over Native Image"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "A question from the audience asked about choosing between Semeru and https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/[GraalVM Native Image]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark's perspective:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid ""
"**Choose Native Image when:**\n"
"- Near-instant startup is critical\n"
"- Your application fits within Native Image's constraints"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Near-instant startup is critical"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Your application fits within Native Image's constraints"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Choose Semeru when:**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "You need full Java specification compliance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Your application uses dynamic class loading"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "You want JIT optimization for your specific workload"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "You need to support existing applications without modification"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Build time is a concern"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Quarkus makes both options easy, so the choice depends on your specific requirements."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Eclipse OMR: The Foundation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Mark also introduced https://www.eclipse.org/omr/[Eclipse OMR], the language-agnostic runtime components that underpin OpenJ9. This ~1 million line codebase provides:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Garbage collection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Threading libraries"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Platform porting layers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Compiler infrastructure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "While OMR hasn't been widely adopted by other language runtimes, it represents a significant investment in reusable runtime technology and includes JitBuilder, a library for rapidly creating JIT compilers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Key Takeaways"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**IBM Semeru Runtimes is a free, open-source Java distribution** based on OpenJDK with the Eclipse OpenJ9 JVM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**OpenJ9 prioritizes balanced performance** across startup, memory, throughput, and ramp-up time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**The shared classes cache dramatically improves startup** by caching loaded classes and JIT-compiled code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Training runs populate the cache** for subsequent warm runs to benefit from."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Layered caches work naturally with container architectures**, enabling efficient distribution and memory sharing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Quarkus integration is trivial** - just set `quarkus.package.jar.aot.enabled=true`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Running Quarkus integration tests automatically creates a good training run**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**Performance improvements are significant** - faster startup, lower memory, better ramp-up."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**The technology is production-proven** - in use since 2005 across hundreds of IBM products."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "**It's a different trade-off than Native Image** - full JVM compliance with excellent startup and memory characteristics."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Conclusion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "IBM Semeru Runtimes and Eclipse OpenJ9 represent a mature, production-proven alternative to HotSpot that delivers significant improvements in startup time and memory footprint without sacrificing Java compatibility. The shared classes cache technology, refined over nearly two decades, provides a compelling option for cloud deployments where these metrics directly impact cost."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "The recent Quarkus integration makes it easier than ever to try Semeru – just swap the JVM and enable AOT. The Quarkus team is planning to run their own benchmarks to quantify the improvements, and Mark encouraged the community to try it and share feedback."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "For applications that need fast startup and low memory but want to stay within the full Java specification, Semeru offers a compelling middle ground between traditional JVMs and Native Image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: _posts/2026-06-16-quarkus-insights-251-semeru-openj9.adoc
msgid "Watch the full episode on the https://www.youtube.com/quarkusio[Quarkus YouTube channel]. Download IBM Semeru Runtimes at https://developer.ibm.com/languages/java/semeru-runtimes/[developer.ibm.com/languages/java/semeru-runtimes] and learn more about Eclipse OpenJ9 at https://www.eclipse.org/openj9/[eclipse.org/openj9]."
msgstr ""
